content.webTitle: CD: Rock review: Of Montreal, Skeletal Lamping

fields.headline: Rock review: Of Montreal, Skeletal Lamping
fields.bodyText: This Athens, Georgia six-piece are fronted by cross-dressing Kevin Barnes, their take on indie rock as flamboyant as his sexually confused alter-ego Georgie Fruit. Barnes pushes their ninth album to sometimes unlistenable extremes and although it has its moments – 'Touched Something's Hollow' is a beauty – the pleasures to be gained from this sexual experiment are few.
